info       = "<html><body><table><tr><td>Drug:</td><td>B05CA02</td></tr><td>route:</td><td>oral</td></tr><tr><td>n-compartments</td><td>1</td></tr></table><p>Chlorhexidine is a bisbiguanide antiseptic and disinfectant used primarily for skin disinfection before surgery and for sterilizing surgical instruments. It is also widely used as a topical antimicrobial agent in mouthwashes for gingivitis. Chlorhexidine is approved and routinely used today; however, systemic administration is rare due to low absorption and potential toxicity.</p><h4>Pharmacokinetics</h4><p>Pharmacokinetic estimates for healthy adult humans after accidental oral and intravenous exposure, as well as repeat oral and topical usage. Due to very poor oral absorption, limited systemic PK data exist. Typical PK parameters are modeled based on known ADME features and preclinical/infrequent clinical reports.</p><h4>References</h4><ol><li><p>Aldeen Salaymeh, E, et al., &amp; Abu Ammar, A (2025). Chlorhexidine-loaded microneedles for treatment of oral diseases. <i>International journal of pharmaceutics</i> 670 125143–None. DOI:<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijpharm.2024.125143\">10.1016/j.ijpharm.2024.125143</a>  PUBMED:<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39732215/\">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39732215</a></p></li><li><p>Betcher, DL, &amp; Burnham, N (1990). Chlorhexidine. <i>Journal of pediatric oncology nursing : official journal of the Association of Pediatric Oncology Nurses</i> 7(2) 82–83. DOI:<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1177/104345429000700227\">10.1177/104345429000700227</a>  PUBMED:<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2363891/\">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2363891</a></p></li><li><p>Reda, B, et al., &amp; Volmer, DA (2020). Determination of chlorhexidine retention in different oral sites using matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization-time of flight mass spectrometry. <i>Archives of oral biology</i> 110 104623–None. DOI:<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.archoralbio.2019.104623\">10.1016/j.archoralbio.2019.104623</a>  PUBMED:<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31830639/\">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31830639</a></p></li></ol></body></html>",
